{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3414807,"name":"","username":"HEFZZJM","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/h/4491bb/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-08-12T15:01:10.661Z","cooked":"<p>Hi everyone. We’re trying to use the pose estimator in the WPIlib to determing the position of our robot. We are using a <span class="abbreviation">LL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Limelight, an integrated vision coprocessor"></template></span> 3G as our vision to adjust the position of our robot. However, we find that it seems that when the position of our robot is inaccurate, calling “addVisionMeasurement()” does not help fix the position of our robot, instead, there seems to be a constant offset between the position measured by our pose estimator seems and the actual pose of our robot. The translation dev used in vision adjustment is porpotional to the ta value from the <span class="abbreviation">LL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Limelight, an integrated vision coprocessor"></template></span>, ranging from 0.003 to 0.2 . I can see from the webUI of the <span class="abbreviation">LL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Limelight, an integrated vision coprocessor"></template></span> that the pose estimated by <span class="abbreviation">LL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Limelight, an integrated vision coprocessor"></template></span> is accurate,at least there isn’t a constant offset between the measured position and the actual one . The state dev used to construct the pose estimator is VecBuilder.fill(0.7, 0.7, 0.1). What could possibly cause the problem?</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":8,"updated_at":"2024-08-12T15:01:10.661Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":133,"reads":135,"readers_count":134,"score":722.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":469757,"topic_slug":"wpilib-pose-estimator-not-reacting-to-vision-updates","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_u