<p>Another potential problem is what you’re passing into the <code>FOM</code> parameter for updateVision. The total area the tag takes up of the <span class="abbreviation">LL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Limelight, an integrated vision coprocessor"></template></span> image is <em>inversely</em> proportional to the camera’s distance from the tag, so closer tags will actually be trusted less since they will have a higher associated deviation. To fix this, just pass k/ta in as the <code>FOM</code> where k is some value (you should tune it later, but for testing you can just pass in, say, 0.1, given your state deviations).</p>
